  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development and subdivision and breaking up of the site would be unacceptable in principle, as it would fail to respond to local distinctiveness with an incongruous layout, scale, appearance and shape, with no regard for the existing street hierarchy, building types, forms and proportions. The proposed development would fail to integrate with the existing urban grain, and the new dwelling would have an unsympathetic, constricted plot shape, and would appear significantly smaller than the rest of the properties on the eastern side of Woodcote Road. The proposal is therefore contrary to policies H1, H2 and D3 of the London Plan 2021, policies 1, 7 and 28 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018 and Supplementary Planning Document 14: Creating Locally Distinctive Places 'Urban Design'.",
    "The proposed development would result in an unsympathetic and constricted plot that is out of character with the surrounding area, and the detailed design of the proposed dwelling including its width, roof shape and fenestration would be at odds with adjacent properties. It is considered that the design of the proposal is therefore unacceptable and would cause harm to the character of Woodcote Avenue and the proposal is contrary to policy D3 of the London Plan 2021, policy 28 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018 and Supplementary Planning Document 14: Creating Locally Distinctive Places 'Urban Design'."
  ],
